election_notes: Registered voters who wish to participate in the American Samoa Caucuses must become members of the territory's Democratic Party. This is a non-governmental process as the territory's election office does not track voters' party affiliation.
Democrats Abroad primary voting runs from March 3 to March 10. Voters must become members of Democrats Abroad and pledge not to participate in any other 2020 presidential primary.
North Dakota does not require voters to register with the state.
Voters in Hawaii do not register a party affiliation, but the Hawaii Democratic Party requires participants in the April 4 primary to be state party members.
